"{\"value\":{\"mdx\":\"# Landscape\\n\\nSeveral technologies exist for image authenticity and provenance. Most solve for different problems, such as edit history, AI detection, trust scoring, rather than proving a photo was authentically captured on a real device.\\n\\nZCAM is a complete solution for mobile photo authenticity. It combines hardware-backed attestation, optional zero-knowledge proofs, and embedded verification into a single system designed for human-taken photos on mobile devices.\\n\\n## Comparison \\n\\n| Approach | Hardware Attestation | ZK Proofs | Embedded Verification | User-friendly Output | Camera Photos | Use Case |\\n|----------|---------------------|-----------|---------------------|---------------|--------------|----------|\\n| **ZCAM** | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | Complete mobile photo authenticity solution |\\n| **C2PA** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | Edit history and provenance |\\n| **Physical Cameras** | ❓ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ✅ | Hardware signed capture with limited support |\\n| **JPEG Trust** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | Trust evaluation framework |\\n| **SynthID** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | AI watermarking and detection |\\n| **AI Content Marking** | ❌ | ❌ | ✅ | ❌ | ❌ | Labeling AI-generated content |\\n\\n## Other Approaches\\n\\n### C2PA\\n\\nC2PA is a standard for creating a verifiable history of an image. It is not specific to authentic photos and applies equally to camera captures and AI-generated images. As an image evolves (cropping, brightness adjustments, etc.), C2PA-compatible editors attach new signed manifests tracking each change.\\n\\nZCAM uses C2PA as its container format but adds hardware-backed guarantees. Where C2PA tracks history with any signing key, ZCAM guarantees the photo was captured on a specific device using keys that can't be extracted or forged.\\n\\n### JPEG Trust\\n\\nJPEG Trust is a framework for evaluating image trustworthiness. It works on top of C2PA, using manifest data to generate trust scores. It is an evaluation layer, not a capture or verification system, and could work alongside ZCAM-generated manifests.\\n\\n\\n### SynthID\\n\\nSynthID, developed by Google, embeds invisible watermarks into AI-generated images. Unlike metadata-based approaches, these watermarks survive cropping and editing. A separate model analyzes images to determine whether they're AI-generated.\\nSynthID focuses on AI detection with probabilistic results. ZCAM focuses on authenticity with cryptographic guarantees.\\n\\n\\n### AI Content Marking\\n\\nSeveral companies provide solutions for marking AI-generated content, using different approaches:\\n\\n- **Meta** adds durable watermarks specifically to AI-generated content. \\n- **OpenAI** generates C2PA-compatible images with DALL-E and ChatGPT.\\n\\nThese solutions label AI content, whereas ZCAM verifies human-captured photos.\\n\\n\\n## When to Use ZCAM\\n\\nZCAM is the right choice when you need:\\n\\n- Hardware-backed proof that a photo was taken on a real device\\n- Cryptographic verification rather than probabilistic detection\\n- A mobile-first solution\\n\\nOther approaches may be more optimized for marking AI-generated content (SynthID, AI Content Marking), tracking edit history (C2PA), or non-mobile platforms.\",\"document\":[{\"href\":\"/overview/landscape#landscape\",\"html\":\"</header>\\n<p>Several technologies exist for image authenticity and provenance. Most solve for different problems, such as edit history, AI detection, trust scoring, rather than proving a photo was authentically captured on a real device.</p>\\n<p>ZCAM is a complete solution for mobile photo authenticity. It combines hardware-backed attestation, optional zero-knowledge proofs, and embedded verification into a single system designed for human-taken photos on mobile devices.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/landscape.mdx#landscape\",\"isPage\":true,\"text\":\"\\nSeveral technologies exist for image authenticity and provenance. Most solve for different problems, such as edit history, AI detection, trust scoring, rather than proving a photo was authentically captured on a real device.\\nZCAM is a complete solution for mobile photo authenticity. It combines hardware-backed attestation, optional zero-knowledge proofs, and embedded verification into a single system designed for human-taken photos on mobile devices.\\n\",\"title\":\"Landscape\",\"titles\":[]},{\"href\":\"/overview/landscape#comparison\",\"html\":\"\\n<table><thead><tr><th>Approach</th><th>Hardware Attestation</th><th>ZK Proofs</th><th>Embedded Verification</th><th>User-friendly Output</th><th>Camera Photos</th><th>Use Case</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><strong>ZCAM</strong></td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>Complete mobile photo authenticity solution</td></tr><tr><td><strong>C2PA</strong></td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>Edit history and provenance</td></tr><tr><td><strong>Physical Cameras</strong></td><td>❓</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>Hardware signed capture with limited support</td></tr><tr><td><strong>JPEG Trust</strong></td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>✅</td><td>Trust evaluation framework</td></tr><tr><td><strong>SynthID</strong></td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>AI watermarking and detection</td></tr><tr><td><strong>AI Content Marking</strong></td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>✅</td><td>❌</td><td>❌</td><td>Labeling AI-generated content</td></tr></tbody></table>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/landscape.mdx#comparison\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nApproachHardware AttestationZK ProofsEmbedded VerificationUser-friendly OutputCamera PhotosUse CaseZCAM✅✅✅✅✅Complete mobile photo authenticity solutionC2PA❌❌✅❌✅Edit history and provenancePhysical Cameras❓❌✅❌✅Hardware signed capture with limited supportJPEG Trust❌❌✅✅✅Trust evaluation frameworkSynthID❌❌✅❌❌AI watermarking and detectionAI Content Marking❌❌✅❌❌Labeling AI-generated content\\n\",\"title\":\"Comparison\",\"titles\":[\"Landscape\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/landscape#other-approaches\",\"html\":\"\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/landscape.mdx#other-approaches\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\n\",\"title\":\"Other Approaches\",\"titles\":[\"Landscape\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/landscape#c2pa\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>C2PA is a standard for creating a verifiable history of an image. It is not specific to authentic photos and applies equally to camera captures and AI-generated images. As an image evolves (cropping, brightness adjustments, etc.), C2PA-compatible editors attach new signed manifests tracking each change.</p>\\n<p>ZCAM uses C2PA as its container format but adds hardware-backed guarantees. Where C2PA tracks history with any signing key, ZCAM guarantees the photo was captured on a specific device using keys that can&#x27;t be extracted or forged.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/landscape.mdx#c2pa\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nC2PA is a standard for creating a verifiable history of an image. It is not specific to authentic photos and applies equally to camera captures and AI-generated images. As an image evolves (cropping, brightness adjustments, etc.), C2PA-compatible editors attach new signed manifests tracking each change.\\nZCAM uses C2PA as its container format but adds hardware-backed guarantees. Where C2PA tracks history with any signing key, ZCAM guarantees the photo was captured on a specific device using keys that can&#x27;t be extracted or forged.\\n\",\"title\":\"C2PA\",\"titles\":[\"Landscape\",\"Other Approaches\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/landscape#jpeg-trust\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>JPEG Trust is a framework for evaluating image trustworthiness. It works on top of C2PA, using manifest data to generate trust scores. It is an evaluation layer, not a capture or verification system, and could work alongside ZCAM-generated manifests.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/landscape.mdx#jpeg-trust\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nJPEG Trust is a framework for evaluating image trustworthiness. It works on top of C2PA, using manifest data to generate trust scores. It is an evaluation layer, not a capture or verification system, and could work alongside ZCAM-generated manifests.\\n\",\"title\":\"JPEG Trust\",\"titles\":[\"Landscape\",\"Other Approaches\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/landscape#synthid\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>SynthID, developed by Google, embeds invisible watermarks into AI-generated images. Unlike metadata-based approaches, these watermarks survive cropping and editing. A separate model analyzes images to determine whether they&#x27;re AI-generated.\\nSynthID focuses on AI detection with probabilistic results. ZCAM focuses on authenticity with cryptographic guarantees.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/landscape.mdx#synthid\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nSynthID, developed by Google, embeds invisible watermarks into AI-generated images. Unlike metadata-based approaches, these watermarks survive cropping and editing. A separate model analyzes images to determine whether they&#x27;re AI-generated.\\nSynthID focuses on AI detection with probabilistic results. ZCAM focuses on authenticity with cryptographic guarantees.\\n\",\"title\":\"SynthID\",\"titles\":[\"Landscape\",\"Other Approaches\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/landscape#ai-content-marking\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>Several companies provide solutions for marking AI-generated content, using different approaches:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Meta</strong> adds durable watermarks specifically to AI-generated content.</li>\\n<li><strong>OpenAI</strong> generates C2PA-compatible images with DALL-E and ChatGPT.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>These solutions label AI content, whereas ZCAM verifies human-captured photos.</p>\\n\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/landscape.mdx#ai-content-marking\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nSeveral companies provide solutions for marking AI-generated content, using different approaches:\\n\\nMeta adds durable watermarks specifically to AI-generated content.\\nOpenAI generates C2PA-compatible images with DALL-E and ChatGPT.\\n\\nThese solutions label AI content, whereas ZCAM verifies human-captured photos.\\n\",\"title\":\"AI Content Marking\",\"titles\":[\"Landscape\",\"Other Approaches\"]},{\"href\":\"/overview/landscape#when-to-use-zcam\",\"html\":\"\\n<p>ZCAM is the right choice when you need:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Hardware-backed proof that a photo was taken on a real device</li>\\n<li>Cryptographic verification rather than probabilistic detection</li>\\n<li>A mobile-first solution</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Other approaches may be more optimized for marking AI-generated content (SynthID, AI Content Marking), tracking edit history (C2PA), or non-mobile platforms.</p>\",\"id\":\"docs/pages/overview/landscape.mdx#when-to-use-zcam\",\"isPage\":false,\"text\":\"\\nZCAM is the right choice when you need:\\n\\nHardware-backed proof that a photo was taken on a real device\\nCryptographic verification rather than probabilistic detection\\nA mobile-first solution\\n\\nOther approaches may be more optimized for marking AI-generated content (SynthID, AI Content Marking), tracking edit history (C2PA), or non-mobile platforms.\",\"title\":\"When to Use ZCAM\",\"titles\":[\"Landscape\"]}]}}"
